  "response": "An IQ score of 121 on the Reynolds Intellectual Assessment Scales (RIAS) is considered **above average** and falls within the **Superior** range of intellectual functioning. Here\u2019s a breakdown of what this score means:\n\n### IQ Score Ranges:\n- **130 and above:** Very Superior  \n- **120-129:** Superior  \n- **110-119:** High Average  \n- **90-109:** Average  \n- **80-89:** Low Average  \n- **70-79:** Borderline  \n- **Below 70:** Extremely Low  \n\n### Interpretation of a 121 IQ:\n- **Percentile Rank:** An IQ of 121 places you in the **92nd percentile**, meaning you scored higher than approximately **92%** of the population.  \n- **Strengths:** Individuals with this level of IQ typically demonstrate strong problem-solving skills, abstract reasoning, and the ability to grasp complex concepts.  \n- **Implications:** This score suggests you are well-suited for academic and professional environments that require analytical thinking, creativity, and intellectual engagement.  \n\nOverall, an IQ of 121 is a strong indicator of above-average cognitive abilities and positions you well for success in various intellectual and professional pursuits.",
